The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning techniques for playing complex video games, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically proposes the use of transformer networks, which have been widely used in natural language processing (NLP), indicating a possible connection to the sub-category of NLP (cs.CL). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) in existing methods, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep Q networks (DQNs) and policy gradients, which are common techniques in reinforcement learning, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
